OL,3,CIs it 'all over' for online scammers?
OL,4,CSir Geoff Hurst hopes it will be
OL,6,F"They took advantage of my mum because
OL,7,Fshe's deaf. They got her information
OL,8,Foff the internet. It was a love scam,
OL,9,Fand before we knew it, fifty grand of
OL,10,Fher life savings were gone".
OL,12,FToday's new research also shows older
OL,13,Fpeople are the most likely to confront
OL,14,Fscammers, with nearly a quarter (23%)
OL,15,Fof people aged over 65 having done so.
OL,17,FAmy Caton is from BT Group - who
OL,18,Fjoined with AbilityNet to run today's
OL,19,Fsession. She urges restraint when
OL,20,Fconfronting fraudsters.
